	<TextInfo>
		<Text Type="Business Summary" lastModified="2015-08-28T08:50:07">Hardy Oil and Gas plc is an international oil and gas company whose operating assets are in India. The Company's portfolio includes a blend of appraisal and development assets. The Company is organized into two business units: India and United Kingdom. The India business unit is operated by the wholly owned subsidiary, Hardy Exploration &amp; Production (India) Inc., and focuses on exploration and production of oil and gas assets in India. The United Kingdom business unit is the holding company and operates in the United Kingdom. Its exploration licenses include D3, PY-3, GS-01 and CY-OS/2. The D3 exploration license encompasses an area of approximately 3,200 square kilometers. The PY-3 field covers an area of approximately 80 square kilometers. The GS-01 exploration license is located in the Gujarat- Saurashtra offshore basin off the west coast of India. The Company holds around 75% interest in CY-OS/2 through its wholly owned subsidiary Hardy Exploration &amp; Production (India) Inc.</Text>
		<Text Type="Financial Summary" lastModified="2016-01-04T00:58:05">BRIEF: For the six months ended 30 September 2015, Hardy Oil &amp; Gas plc revenues was not reported. Net loss increased from $1.4M to $4.2M. Higher net loss reflects India segment loss increase of 55% to $558K. Basic Earnings per Share excluding Extraordinary Items decreased from -$0.02 to -$0.11.</Text>
